## Why This Is Asked
Tests ability to design a compliant, Azure-native data marketplace with per-tenant contracts, schema evolution, and privacy controls.

## Key Concepts
- Azure Data Lake Gen2, Purview, Schema Registry
- Per-tenant contracts, dynamic schema evolution
- Row-level masking, aggregated signals exposure
- Azure ML centralized model registry, BYOK, cross-region DR

## Code Example
```javascript
function maskRow(row, tenantId) {
  if (row.tenantId !== tenantId) return row;
  row.ssn = null;
  row.email = row.email ? row.email.replace(/^[^@]+@/, "***@"): row.email;
  return row;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you implement schema evolution without breaking existing contracts?
- What would you monitor to detect drift between contract expectations and ingested data?
